.TH AEGIX-BACKUP 8 "2026-07-24" "aegix-backup" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
aegix\-backup \- encrypted, tested\-restore disaster recovery for Aegix/Artix Linux (runit)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aegix\-backup
.RI [ \-\-dry\-run ]
.I command
.RI [ target ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B aegix\-backup
maintains a three\-legged, fully encrypted disaster\-recovery setup from one
config file and one nightly cron entry:
.IP \(bu 2
.B Bootable clones
\(em complete, independently bootable copies of the running system on an
internal second disk and/or an external drive (LUKS2). After every sync the
clone's boot chain (fstab, crypttab, GRUB for both BIOS and UEFI, plus a
portable fallback initramfs) is repointed at the clone's own UUIDs and
verified, so bootability is re\-earned nightly rather than assumed.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Encrypted offsite
\(em a restic repository on an always\-present internal LUKS disk, mirrored to
a private Hugging Face dataset repo. Only ciphertext ever leaves the machine.
Optional.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Notes to a git remote.
Optional.
.PP
A clone
.B mirrors its source
: btrfs @/@home systems clone via read\-only subvolume snapshots; plain
filesystems (e.g. stock ext4\-on\-LUKS) clone live in a single
.BR rsync (1)
run with
.BR \-x .
Mixed source/target layouts are refused. Clone targets that are not attached
are skipped, not errors, so the nightly succeeds whether or not a travel drive
is plugged in.
.PP
The guiding principle:
.B a backup you have not booted is a hypothesis, not a backup.
Boot your clone once, on purpose, while the original still works.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B preflight
Check binaries, config sanity and per\-leg prerequisites. Legs that are not
configured are skipped, not failed.
.TP
.B status
One\-glance answer to \(lqhow did the last nightly go?\(rq: the last recorded
result plus the per\-leg summary of the most recent completed daily run.
.TP
.BR clone\-daily ", " clone\-weekly
Clone the running system to every configured target and make each bootable.
.B clone\-weekly
applies fewer excludes (see
.BR EXCLUDE_HOME_DAILY_EXTRA ).
.TP
.BI clone\-bootfix " \fR[\fPtarget\fR]\fP"
Re\-apply bootability (fstab/crypttab/GRUB/initramfs) to one or all targets
without an rsync.
.TP
.BI clone\-browse " target\fR,\fP " clone\-unbrowse " target"
Mount a clone read\-only under
.I /mnt/aegix\-browse/<target>
for inspection, and release it. Internal targets are deliberately never
auto\-mounted.
.TP
.B videos
Add\-only top\-up of the Videos directory to the external drive.
.TP
.B pictures
restic backup of the configured sources into the local repo, retention prune,
then mirror the (ciphertext) repo to the Hugging Face remote, regenerating
DO\-NOT\-DELETE guard files.
.TP
.B notes\-push
Commit and push the notes repository. Refuses to push if anything under the
configured plaintext\-vault directory has become tracked.
.TP
.B ext\-snapshot
Dated btrfs snapshots of the external clone with retention (btrfs targets
only).
.TP
.BR daily ", " now
The nightly set: notes, clones (weekly variant on Sundays), external
snapshot, pictures. Installed as
.IR /etc/cron.daily/aegix\-backup ;
anacron catches up missed days.
.TP
.BR automount\-up ", " automount\-down ", " automount\-sync
Used by the udev/runit plumbing: plugging the external drive in mounts it
read\-only at the configured browse mountpoint; unplugging cleans up.
.TP
.B local\-up
Unlock and mount the internal restic disk (run at boot by a runit one\-shot;
crypttab is not processed on Artix/runit).
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Prefix: print the actions a command would take without performing them.
.SH CONFIGURATION
All behaviour is driven by
.IR /etc/aegix\-backup.conf
(root\-only, mode 0600). Start from
.I aegix\-backup.conf.example
in the repository \(em every hard\-won lesson is documented next to the knob it
protects. Identify disks by
.B UUID, model or serial, never by device name
.RI ( /dev/nvme0n1
vs
.IR /dev/nvme1n1
is not stable across reboots). The notes and pictures/offsite legs are
optional: leave their variables unset for a clone\-only install.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/aegix\-backup.conf
Configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/cron.daily/aegix\-backup
Nightly entry (via cronie + anacron).
.TP
.I /etc/cryptsetup\-keys.d/*.key
Keyfiles for unattended unlocks. Each clone target also needs a passphrase
keyslot \(em a keyfile on the dead machine's encrypted root helps nobody.
.TP
.I /var/log/aegix\-backup/aegix\-backup.log
Log.
.TP
.I RECOVERY.md
The recovery runbook. Read it now, not during the disaster, and keep a copy
somewhere that is not the machine being recovered.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
sudo aegix\-backup preflight
sudo aegix\-backup \-\-dry\-run daily
sudo aegix\-backup clone\-daily
sudo aegix\-backup status
sudo aegix\-backup clone\-browse external
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cryptsetup (8),
.BR rsync (1),
.BR restic (1),
.BR btrfs (8),
.BR anacron (8)
.PP
